4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO HOME INSPECTIONS;
5 ALIGNING THE HOME INSPECTION PROGRAM WITH OTHER DEPARTMENTAL LICENSING PROGRAMS;
6 PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; PROVIDING FEES; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; REVISING LAW
7 RELATED TO HOME INSPECTION LICENSURE; INCREASING THE MINIMUM COVERAGE AMOUNT FOR
8 ERRORS AND OMISSIONS INSURANCE; PROVIDING STANDARDS FOR THE PRACTICE OF HOME
9 INSPECTIONS; AMENDING SECTIONS 37-1-401, 39-9-101, 39-9-102, 39-9-206, 39-9-207, 39-9-301, AND
10 39-9-303, MCA; REPEALING SECTIONS 39-9-212 AND 39-9-213, MCA; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED
11 EFFECTIVE DATE.”
